data.description: WELCOME To this Charming home in Conway's Historic district.  Sitting on a corner lot, this home features the original Hardwood flooring in the Living Room and the Dining Room. The kitchen features a Gas Range, Microwave, Pantry and plenty of cabinetry and a spacious breakfast room.  There are two bedrooms and a bath downstairs and a bedroom/bonus room upstairs with a bathroom.  This home has been well maintained and has been updated with fresh paint, carpet and vinyl flooring recently and over the past few years. Many other features include a 3-ton Central Heat & Air system (2 years), Multiple ceiling fans throughout, 30-amp RV hookups, underground utilities, three garages, storage building and a fenced yard.  Step outside to enjoy the covered patio, extended patio, deck & covered front porch! This property would be a great INVESTMENT property being only a few blocks from Hendrix College.  Priced below the Appraisal Price.
